cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.COMM, cs.SY, cs.DC 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper proposes a novel optimization technique for beamforming at the satellite to support interference mitigation techniques. This falls under the domain of information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper deals with designing an on-board beam generation process for multibeam satellite systems to reduce traffic at the feeder link. This involves networking and internet architecture aspects. 
3. cs.COMM (Communication and Networking): The paper proposes a solution to increase the total throughput of multibeam satellite systems. This falls under the domain of communication and networking. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper deals with designing an on-board processing system for multibeam satellite systems. This involves systems and control aspects. 
5. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper proposes a solution to reduce the payload cost and complexity of multibeam satellite systems. This involves distributed, parallel, and cluster computing aspects.
